            <h5 class="mb-0">
                <a class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                    How do can I join the Notifly Family?
                </a>
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingThree">
            <div class="card-body">
                Here is the Step By Step Process:<br /><br />
                1. Open up Notifly Application<br />
                2. Register an account<br />
                <img scr="~/img/registration_notifly1.jpg" width="100" height="100" /><br />
                3. On the top border, click on the Groups button<br />
                4. On the bottom of page click on 'Create Group' and add in a 'Group Name'<br />
                5. Add the members you would like to be part of the Group Name. A success bar will pop up when each member is added.<br />
                6. Once done, SAVE your changes.<br />
                7. Go Back to Groups page and check if your group has been added to your account.<br />
                8. [Optional] Incase you want to make changes to the your group, 'Group Details' by your Group Name to add, edit, or remove any group members.<br />
                9. [Optional] Double Check to make sure everything looks correct.<br />
                10. On your phone go to your messaging app with the format below, text your friends/ coworkers/etc.<br />
                Event Name:                 @*<img scr="~/img/registration_notifly1.jpg" width="100" height="100" align="middle" /><br />*@
                Date and Time:<br />
                Venue:<br />
                City, State<br />
                Group Name:(What you created in the app)<br />
                11. And just like that, your event is sent to all the members added to the group.<br />
                12. On the recipients end, they will get a message and must reply with a 'yes [identification number]' or 'no [identification number]'<br />
                13. In the Website, go to RSVP to view all that are attending to the event.<br />
                14. And just like that, you are done! <br /><br />
                The more groups you add, the easier it is to set up an events on the fly.<br />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
